The paper presents a distributed algorithm for computing topological information in a synchronous network, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm deals with distances and connectivity in networks, which is a common topic in network science and graph theory, suggesting categories such as network science (cs.NI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and algorithms (cs.AL) as likely sub-categories.
